757. Re recent Cabinet change and return of Ben Gurion to direct participation in government (Embtel 698The Embassy in Tel Aviv notified the Department on February 18 that the Israeli Government the preceding evening, February 17, had announced Lavon’s resignation as Minister of Defense, and that he had been replaced by Ben-Gurion, whose appointment “had not been anticipated.” (Ibid., 784A.5/2–1855)), Gaza incident (Embtel 737See footnote 2, Document 33.), and my talk with Prime Minister Sharett March 3 (Embtel 754
Supra.
).
